{
  "texts": [
    "Bone Microstructure AnalysisMorphological 3D parameters were quantified from the CBCT-imaged ex vivo test set, using conventional image processing, and SR.",
    "The true microstructure was analyzed using high-resolution µCT imaging.",
    "The volumes were binarized using the Otsu threshold [48].",
    "An ad-hoc Python script was used to calculate the recommended morphological parameters: bone volume fraction (BV/TV), trabecular thickness (Tb.Th), trabecular separation (Tb.Sp), and trabecular number (Tb.N) [49].",
    "In the case of the 2D models, the parameters were assessed for the axial 2D predictions as well as an average of the predictions of the three orthogonal planes."
  ]
}